# OpenAI

[Usage metrics](https://platform.openai.com/docs/api-reference/usage) from OpenAI. The dashboard contains:

- Invocation rates
- Top Project, User and API IDs
- Token usage statistics
- Usage metrics for language models, embedding models, image models, audio speech models, audio transcriptions models, etc

embeddableConfig.description: Visualizes the overall request volume. Vector stores and code interpreter sessions are excluded from this chart and other charts that mention invocations, as they lack fields to determine the invocation count.
Visualizes overall token usage, showing sum of input (including embedding and moderation), audio input, audio output and output tokens.

Visualization shows the top 10 object types across various data streams where the "num_model_requests" field is present. Vector store and code interpreter sessions are excluded from this chart since they do not contain this field.
Visualizes request volume over time by model
Usage visualizations for text-generation, audio-generation, embedding and moderation based models. The visualizations highlight key token consumption patterns and usage trends.
Visualizes token usage over time, showing input, audio input (including embedding and moderation), cached input, audio output and output tokens to highlight trends in model activity.

attributes.description: Visualizes overall token usage, showing input (including embedding and moderation), audio input, cached input, audio output and output tokens to highlight the distribution ratio.

Visualizes token usage over time and grouped by model, showing input (including embedding and moderation), audio input, cached input, audio output and output tokens to highlight trends in model activity.
